Avalanche kills one skier in northwest Italy . One skier was killed and six others were slightly injured on Saturday when an avalanche came crashing down on an Alpine ski area in northwest Italy , police said . A huge piece of a glacier broke off and slammed into the slopes of the Courmayeur ski area , which was packed with hundreds of skiers taking advantage of sunny weather . Police said the victim , whose identity was not immediately known , was crushed against a tree by the avalanche . The injured were airlifed by helicopter to Courmayeur where they were being treated for minor injuries . 
